    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 was used to process LC\u2013MS/MS runs and MassIVE datasets provided in mzML or mzXML format. Feature detection in SIRIUS 4 is similar in spirit to a targeted analysis. Instead of searching for all features in a run, SIRIUS first collects all fragmentation spectra and their precursor information and then searches for features that are associated with those fragmentation spectra (precursor ions, adduct ions and isotope peaks).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes SIRIUS's data ingestion and feature detection workflow for LC-MS/MS data (mzML/mzXML formats), but does not discuss internal Java framework implementation details or the specific structured representation format used internally.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does SIRIUS ingest and parse LC-MS/MS data into a structured representation within its Java framework?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:25:51.501565+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 was used to process LC\u2013MS/MS runs and MassIVE datasets provided in mzML or mzXML format.",
      "asbval:note": "SIRIUS is confirmed as a tool used in the paper for processing LC-MS/MS data.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "SIRIUS",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:25:51.501565+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Feature detection in SIRIUS 4 is similar in spirit to a targeted analysis. Instead of searching for all features in a run, SIRIUS first collects all fragmentation spectra and their precursor information and then searches for features that are associated with those fragmentation spectra (precursor ions, adduct ions and isotope peaks). Adducts and isotopes were detected using predefined lists of mass differences. Fragmentation spectra assigned to the same feature (precursor ion) are merged using an agglomerative clustering algorithm based on cosine distance.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes SIRIUS's output as structured feature detection with MS1/MS/MS hierarchies (precursor ions, adducts, isotopes, fragmentation spectra), but does not explicitly name the output format as 'SIRIUS-native format' or provide technical details about the internal data structure representation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Parsed and structured spectral data representation in SIRIUS-native format with validated MS1 and MS/MS hierarchies",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:25:51.501565+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 was used to process LC\u2013MS/MS runs and MassIVE datasets provided in mzML or mzXML format. Feature detection in SIRIUS 4 is similar in spirit to a targeted analysis. Instead of searching for all features in a run, SIRIUS first collects all fragmentation spectra and their precursor information and then searches for features that are associated with those fragmentation spectra (precursor ions, adduct ions and isotope peaks).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes SIRIUS's role in the LC-MS/MS analysis pipeline (feature detection, data ingestion), but the paper's primary focus is on COSMIC (confidence scoring workflow), not on reconstructing or detailing SIRIUS's internal pipeline architecture.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct the LC-MS/MS metabolite analysis pipeline entry point in SIRIUS",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:25:51.501565+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card frames the task as reconstructing SIRIUS's internal data ingestion and parsing mechanisms, but the paper uses SIRIUS as a component tool within the broader COSMIC workflow. The paper does not provide implementation-level details about SIRIUS's Java framework or internal data structure design.",
        "The paper describes SIRIUS's functional role (feature detection, MS/MS processing) but does not focus on or provide detailed technical documentation of SIRIUS's entry point or internal structured representation format.",
        "The research question and title suggest a deep dive into SIRIUS internals, but the paper treats SIRIUS as a black-box tool applied to metabolomics data as part of the COSMIC annotation workflow."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:25:51.501565+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
