    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/api-endpoint-communication/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "CSI:FingerID15, which is best-of-class among in silico methods18, does not rely on such information. Second, we have to separate correct and incorrect annotations, as is the case for library search or peptide annotation in shotgun proteomics; this allows one to concentrate downstream analysis on novel compounds most likely to be correctly annotated.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper extensively describes CSI:FingerID as an in silico method used within the COSMIC workflow for structure ranking, but does not describe it as a remote web service endpoint or discuss API submission. CSI:FingerID is used locally as part of SIRIUS processing, not as a separate web service to be called remotely.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
