    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hierarchical-spectrum-object-construction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 was used to process LC\u2013MS/MS runs and MassIVE datasets provided in mzML or mzXML format. Feature detection in SIRIUS 4 is similar in spirit to a targeted analysis. Instead of searching for all features in a run, SIRIUS first collects all fragmentation spectra and their precursor information and then searches for features that are associated with those fragmentation spectra (precursor ions, adduct ions and isotope peaks).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes SIRIUS processing LC-MS/MS data and organizing spectra with precursor/fragment information, but does not explicitly detail 'hierarchical spectrum object construction' or 'in-memory data structures' as a discrete task. The paper uses SIRIUS as a tool for processing but does not frame spectrum object construction as a standalone skill or workflow step.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
