      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 was used to process LC\u2013MS/MS runs and MassIVE datasets provided in mzML or mzXML format... We use both isotope patterns and fragmentation patterns to determine the molecular formula de novo using SIRIUS 4 with default parameters and mass accuracy of 10 ppm.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SIRIUS ingests mzML/mzXML, constructs fragmentation trees, and determines molecular formulas. However, the paper does NOT emphasize metadata validation as a primary function; instead it focuses on molecular formula determination and fragmentation tree computation. The card overstates the validation role.",
