    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-query-formulation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Untargeted metabolomics experiments rely on spectral libraries for structure annotation, but, typically, only a small fraction of spectra can be matched... Here we introduce the COSMIC workflow that combines in silico structure database generation and annotation with a confidence score consisting of kernel density P value estimation and a support vector machine with enforced directionality of features.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper does address the problem of annotating metabolites absent from spectral libraries using high-resolution MS/MS data, but the solution is COSMIC (combining SIRIUS, CSI:FingerID, and confidence scoring), not MSNovelist-based query formulation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometry-query-formulation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You have a high-resolution LC-MS/MS experiment with a measured [M+H]+ or [M-H]\u2212 ion mass and optionally a parent ion fragmentation spectrum (peak list with m/z and intensity pairs), and you seek to generate candidate molecular structures for an unknown metabolite that may not be ",
