    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-fingerprint-parsing/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "CSI:FingerID15, which is best-of-class among in silico methods18, does not rely on such information... we present the COSMIC (Confidence Of Small Molecule IdentifiCations) workflow that combines selection or generation of a structure database, searching in the structure database with CSI:FingerID and a confidence score to differentiate between correct and incorrect annotations.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses CSI:FingerID for fingerprint-based structure ranking and annotation, but the primary focus is on COSMIC's confidence scoring layer applied to CSI:FingerID outputs, not on parsing CSI:FingerID web service responses per se. The paper does not describe a task of extracting and parsing raw fingerprint predictions from a web service endpoint.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "molecular-fingerprint-parsing",
