        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/structured-result-validation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 was used to process LC\u2013MS/MS runs and MassIVE datasets provided in mzML or mzXML format.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SIRIUS is used (SIRIUS 4 specifically) and is Java-based, but does NOT describe SIRIUS as submitting queries to CANOPUS or performing result validation before displaying annotations. The paper describes SIRIUS's role in feature detection, molecular formula determination, and CSI:FingerID ranking, but not integration with CANOPUS or validation of CANOPUS results. The card's claim about SIRIUS-CANOPUS integration and validation is not supported by the paper.",
