    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/vendor-format-to-standard-conversion/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 was used to process LC\u2013MS/MS runs and MassIVE datasets provided in mzML or mzXML format. Feature detection in SIRIUS 4 is similar in spirit to a targeted analysis. Instead of searching for all features in a run, SIRIUS first collects all fragmentation spectra and their precursor information and then searches for features that are associated with those fragmentation spectra (precursor ions, adduct ions and isotope peaks).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SIRIUS processes mzML/mzXML formats and constructs intermediate representations (fragmentation spectra, precursor info, features). However, the card's framing of 'vendor-format-to-standard-conversion' as a standalone task is not the paper's focus. The paper uses SIRIUS for this as part of the larger COSMIC workflow for metabolite annotation, not as an isolated data conversion step. The card abstracts this as a generic conversion task; the paper treats it as integral to structure annotation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "vendor-format-to-standard-conversion",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Convert raw LC-MS/MS data from vendor-specific formats (mzML, mzXML, or instrument-native formats) into a structured, validated intermediate representation suitable for downstream metabolite analysis.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:32:40.455961+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/vendor-format-to-standard-conversion/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 was used to process LC\u2013MS/MS runs and MassIVE datasets provided in mzML or mzXML format. Feature detection in SIRIUS 4 is similar in spirit to a targeted analysis. Instead of searching for all features in a run, SIRIUS first collects all fragmentation spectra and their precursor information and then searches for features that are associated with those fragmentation spectra (precursor ions, adduct ions and isotope peaks). Adducts and isotopes were detected using predefined lists of mass differences.",
      "asbval:note": "SIRIUS 4 is confirmed to parse mzML/mzXML, collect fragmentation spectra, detect precursor ions, adducts, and isotopes, and construct in-memory representations. The description aligns with the card's characterization of SIRIUS's role.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "vendor-format-to-standard-conversion",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "SIRIUS \u2014 Java framework that accepts LC-MS/MS data via built-in data importer, parses vendor and standard formats, validates spectral metadata, and constructs in-memory spectrum objects",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:32:40.455961+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/vendor-format-to-standard-conversion/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We use both isotope patterns and fragmentation patterns to determine the molecular formula de novo using SIRIUS 4 with default parameters and mass accuracy of 10 ppm. CSI:FingerID with default parameters was used to rank structure candidates.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SIRIUS is used to prepare LC-MS/MS data for molecular formula determination and downstream structure annotation (via CSI:FingerID). Fragmentation tree computation is also mentioned as a key SIRIUS function.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "vendor-format-to-standard-conversion",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When ingesting raw LC-MS/MS output from a mass spectrometry instrument and you need to prepare it for metabolite identification, fragmentation tree computation, or molecular formula annotation.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
