    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/web-service-api-integration/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 was used to process LC\u2013MS/MS runs and MassIVE datasets provided in mzML or mzXML format... CSI:FingerID with default parameters was used to rank structure candidates.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses SIRIUS 4 and CSI:FingerID but does not describe HTTP POST requests, JSON response parsing, or web service API integration. The paper uses SIRIUS as a command-line/integrated tool, not as a programmatic web service client. MSNovelist is not mentioned in the paper. CANOPUS is mentioned only as a complementary tool: 'COSMIC complements compound class annotation tools such as CANOPUS' but is not used in the workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "web-service-api-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Construct and submit HTTP POST requests to SIRIUS web service endpoints (CSI:FingerID, MSNovelist, CANOPUS) to dispatch mass spectrometry queries and parse JSON responses into structured molecular predictions.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:32:55.480741+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/web-service-api-integration/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SIRIUS 4 was used to process LC\u2013MS/MS runs... CSI:FingerID with default parameters was used to rank structure candidates.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SIRIUS 4 is used for LC-MS/MS analysis and integrates CSI:FingerID. However, the paper does not describe SIRIUS as a web service dispatcher or discuss HTTP POST requests. MSNovelist is not mentioned. CANOPUS is mentioned as a separate complementary tool, not integrated into the COSMIC workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "web-service-api-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "SIRIUS (Java-based framework integrating CSI:FingerID, CANOPUS, MSNovelist web services; provides both GUI and CLI for LC-MS/MS analysis and web service dispatch)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:32:55.480741+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/web-service-api-integration/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "CSI:FingerID with default parameters was used to rank structure candidates... COSMIC's confidence score combines E-value estimation and a linear support vector machine (SVM) with enforced directionality... Besides the calibrated score, COSMIC's confidence score uses features such as score differences to other candidates, the total peak intensity explained by the fragmentation tree and the cardinality of the molecular fingerprints.",
      "asbval:note": "CSI:FingerID is confirmed as a tool for molecular fingerprint prediction integrated into SIRIUS workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "web-service-api-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "CSI:FingerID (Web service component for predicting molecular fingerprints from mass spectra using machine learning; integrated into SIRIUS)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:32:55.480741+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/web-service-api-integration/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "MSNovelist is not mentioned anywhere in the paper. The paper does not discuss de-novo structure generation as a separate tool; instead, it uses CSI:FingerID for structure ranking from a database.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "web-service-api-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MSNovelist (Web service component for de-novo structure generation from mass spectra; accepts molecular ion mass and fragmentation data)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:32:55.480741+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/web-service-api-integration/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "COSMIC complements compound class annotation tools such as CANOPUS. COSMIC targets molecular structure annotations but annotates only a fraction of the compounds in a sample; in contrast, CANOPUS annotates practically all compounds in a sample for which fragmentation spectra have been measured but is restricted to annotating compound classes.",
      "asbval:note": "CANOPUS is mentioned as a complementary tool for chemical classification, but it is not integrated into the COSMIC workflow and is not used in the paper's analyses. The paper does not describe CANOPUS as part of SIRIUS or discuss its use.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "web-service-api-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "CANOPUS (Web service component for systematic chemical classification using high-resolution fragmentation mass spectra; integrated into SIRIUS)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:32:55.480741+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/web-service-api-integration/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For each fragmentation spectrum, COSMIC considers only the structure candidate that is top ranked by CSI:FingerID as an annotation... CSI:FingerID and COSMIC are computed here; all other scores are from ref. 18.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms use of molecular fingerprint predictions (CSI:FingerID) from mass spectra. However, the paper does not discuss de-novo structure generation (MSNovelist) or chemical class annotations (CANOPUS) as part of the COSMIC workflow. The paper focuses on structure database searching, not de-novo generation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-021-01045-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "web-service-api-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have a parsed mass spectrum (precursor m/z, ionization mode, collision energy, and fragment peak list as m/z\u2013intensity pairs) and need to obtain molecular fingerprint predictions, de-novo candidate structures, or chemical class annotations without maintaining local neura",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:32:55.480741+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
